Package: waon
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends},
         libfftw3-3,
         libsndfile1,
         libao4,
         libsamplerate0,
         libgtk2.0-0
Description: Wave-to-Notes transcriber
 WaoN is a Wave-to-Notes transcriber, a tool that converts audio files
 (WAV format) into MIDI files by analyzing the frequency spectrum.
 The name "WaoN" also means "harmony of notes" or "chord" in Japanese.
 .
 This package includes:
  - waon: The core command-line transcriber
  - pv: A phase vocoder for pitch shifting and time stretching
  - gwaon: A GTK+ based GUI version of WaoN

Package: libwaon0
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends},
         libfftw3-3,
         libsndfile1
Description: WaoN shared library
 This package contains the shared library for WaoN, which can be used
 by other applications and language bindings.

Package: libwaon-dev
Architecture: any
Section: libdevel
Depends: libwaon0 (= ${binary:Version}),
         ${misc:Depends},
         libfftw3-dev,
         libsndfile1-dev
Description: WaoN development files
 This package contains the development headers and static libraries
 for building applications that use the WaoN library.

Package: python3-waon
Architecture: any
Section: python
Depends: ${python3:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends},
         libwaon0 (= ${binary:Version}),
         python3-numpy
Description: Python bindings for WaoN
 This package contains Python 3 bindings for the WaoN library,
 allowing Python programs to transcribe audio files to MIDI.